President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Tennessee due to severe storms, straight-line winds, and flooding that occurred from May 3 to May 4, 2020. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. The federal funding will be available on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures statewide. Myra M. Shird has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.